    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#title": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "Roderick Cox and the Scottish Symphony | With the NAC Orchestra | Oct 14 - 15, 2026 | Southam Hall"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#image": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "https://naccnaca-eventimages.s3.amazonaws.com/40396/9169_nac_naco_26_27_batch1_7__large.jpg"
      }
    ],
    "http://ogp.me/ns#description": [
      {
        "@language": "en-ca",
        "@value": "A few things to know ...\n\n\n\tNature, poetry, and history come alive in this program of music spanning three centuries.\n\tBe whisked away to Scotland with Mendelssohn’s “Scottish” Symphony—a musical postcard that evokes the country’s misty moors and storm-swept coastline.\n\tJazz, spirituals, and the poetry of Toni Morrison converge in André Previn’s Honey and Rue, featuring soprano soloist Vuvu Mpofu.\n\n\nWhen a 20-year-old Felix Mendelssohn arrived in Scotland for a summer holiday, he was enchanted by the country’s mysterious landscape, which he described as..."
      }
    ],
